        "show_seo_content": true,
        "seo_content": "<h3>What is an upholstered bed?</h3><p>An upholstered bed is a bed frame fully covered in fabric — velvet, chenille, or a textured weave — and padded throughout, giving it a soft, luxurious finish from headboard to base. Unlike a wooden or metal frame, it adds warmth and texture to a bedroom, making it a natural centrepiece rather than just a place to sleep.</p><h3>What fabric and colour options are there?</h3><p>Our upholstered range comes in a selection of fabrics and colourways, from plush velvets to more practical weaves, so you can match the bed to the rest of your room. Each fabric is available in multiple colours — from neutral creams and warm greys to bold blacks and rich jewel tones.</p><h3>What headboard styles are available?</h3><p>We offer wingback, panel, and button-studded headboard designs across our upholstered range. Each style is available in the full selection of fabrics and colours, so you can build the exact look you want for your bedroom.</p><h3>Wingback vs. panel headboard — what's the difference?</h3><p>A wingback headboard has panels that angle out at the sides, creating a more framed, cocooned look and giving you something to lean against side-on. A panel headboard is a flat, neatly stitched design — cleaner and more contemporary, and usually a little more affordable.</p><h3>Do upholstered beds come with storage?</h3><p>Yes — most of our upholstered beds are available with optional built-in storage drawers, typically two or four, positioned on either side of the base. Ottoman versions are also available, where the entire base lifts on gas-lift pistons to reveal a large under-bed compartment.</p><h3>Do upholstered beds come with a mattress?</h3><p>It depends on the listing — some are sold as a complete bed-and-mattress bundle, while others are available as a frame only so you can pair them with a mattress you already own or choose one separately. Check the product options on each listing to see what's included.</p><h3>Are upholstered beds easy to clean?</h3><p>For everyday care, a quick vacuum with an upholstery attachment keeps the fabric fresh. Spills should be blotted immediately with a clean, dry cloth — avoid rubbing. For a deeper clean, a fabric spray or upholstery shampoo works well on most of our fabrics.</p><h3>Are upholstered beds easy to assemble?</h3><p>Yes — all our upholstered beds are designed for straightforward home assembly with basic tools, and the headboard typically brackets on separately. Full step-by-step instructions and all necessary fixings are included with every order.</p>"
